cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language models and their syntactic representations. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses neural networks to model language. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with natural language processing and understanding. The paper also uses a gradient similarity metric, which suggests it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper could be categorized under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as it deals with the organization of syntactic representations in neural language models.
